#Text=Santa Cruz County ( California )
#Text=Santa Cruz County is in California just south of the Bay Area .
#Text=The north half of Monterey Bay is part of the county .
#Text=It is the state 's second-smallest county by land area , with only San Francisco County occupying a smaller physical area .
#Text=Cities

#Text=- Santa Cruz is best known as a countercultural hub , with a fun bohemian feel and youthful vibe , and weekend tourist attractions like the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk , a historic mission , and the dubious Mystery Spot .

#Text=The beaches north and south of Santa Cruz are considered some of the more pristine areas of natural beauty in central California , and while conditions generally make them impractical for swimming , several are considered an expert surfer 's cold cold paradise .
#Text=Other destinations
#Text=Go next
#Text=- Located to the north of Santa Cruz County , San Mateo County has a split personality .

#Text=Its eastern half is a heavily populated urban area , home to Silicon Valley companies , San Francisco International Airport , and all of the hotels , restaurants , malls , and other amenities needed to support a bustling population .

#Text=The western half is completely different , offering an amazing escape for those looking to hike among redwoods , or who want to see seabirds , seals and whales while enjoying a drive along the Pacific Coast Highway , or for couples hoping for a romantic getaway in a quiet B&B .
#Text=- Santa Cruz County 's northern neighbor is home to Silicon Valley , headquarters to hundreds of tech companies including giants like Apple , Intel and Hewlett Packard .

#Text=Visitors will appreciate the massive array of restaurants , museums , and cultural opportunities offered by the huge city of San Jose , while at the other end of the spectrum the tiny town of Gilroy is famous for garlic , with its annual festival attracting over 100,000 garlic lovers .
#Text=- Southeast of Santa Cruz County , San Benito County is an inland county dominated by the Coast Mountain Range .
#Text=It is relatively sparsely populated , with only about 55,000 inhabitants .
#Text=Pinnacles National Park and its dramatic rock formations lies in this county , as well as the town of San Juan Bautista and its historic mission .

#Text=- Located south of Santa Cruz County , Monterey County is what many people think of when they think of the Central Coast - the Monterey Bay Aquarium , the beautiful 17-Mile Drive , Cannery Row , Pebble Beach golf course , and the rugged beauty of Big Sur .

#Text=The northern part of the county contains every manner of amenity for travelers , ranging from chain motels to five star resorts , while the southern portion of the county is remote and accessible mainly by the Pacific Coast Highway or on foot by hikers .
